@NODE Intro "Introduction"

--------------------------------------------------------------------INTRODUCTION

Well, I think there is just enough meat here to actually stick these out
on the net.
 
Icons, maketh thine GUI, and the Amiga has them in spades, and whilst I like a 
little creative disorder and perhaps more than a little style in icons I also 
like a dash of uniformity, just for flavour.

So here they are, My own foray into the icon battlefield
These are all 8 colour MWB icons (Although I prefer my palette a litle
stronger than most. I usually have WBverlauf spread the MWB blue from FF00FF
(Bright Purple) at the top of the screen to 0000FF (Bright blue) at the bottom

Some of the directories are subdivided into 
Old: The first attempts I was kinda happy about.
New: The setup I had for quite a while.
Newest: The setup I'm still developing. 
(Whilst under the influence of Girish Nath)

The backgrounds are from the Amber RPG (I haven't done anything interesting with
the serpent brush, but I'm sure you can emboss it yourselves if you want a 
backdrop like the supplied Unicorn one) except the one called "Olivia" which is
a rendering of a picture by Olivia De Berardinis (Which I just happen to like) I
know it's perhaps a little risque but it has a certian "something" that most 
"cheescake" paintings just dont have. If you find it offensive, wipe it.

@{"Marble1BP" link Background/Marble1BP/main }: A two colour marble for windows.
@{"MarbleLite1BP" link Background/MarbleLite1BP/main }: As above but a little lighter.
@{"MarbleDark1BP" link Background/MarbleDark1BP/main }: I'm sure you can guess.
@{"SherylCrow" link Background/SherylCrow/main }: A pic I found on the net that I think renders down well.
@{"Death" link Background/Death/main }: A nice B/W pic of Death of the Endless.
@{"Death2" link Background/Death2/main }: Another pic (From the postcard you got with "The time of your life").
@{"Sister" link Background/Sister/main }: Shakespears Sister, Some time ago...
@{"AmberUnic" link Background/AmberUnic/main }: The Amber Unicorn.
@{"AmberTexture" link Background/AmberTexture/main }: With a little tinkering.
@{"AmberSerp" link Background/AmberSerp/main }: The Chaos Serpent.

Have a peek, pick and choose, but above all

Enjoy!

